// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/trace/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 6 (per-Connection)
// Spec: sqlite-native.md §22 (operational tooling — sqlite3_trace_v2)
//
// SQLite's `sqlite3_trace_v2(db, mask, callback, ctx)` installs ONE
// callback that fires on a configurable set of events:
//
//   * `Stmt`     — at first VDBE step (SQL text + expanded SQL)
//   * `Profile`  — at last VDBE step (SQL + nanoseconds elapsed)
//   * `Row`      — at each ResultRow opcode (current row payload not
//                  exposed by the C API — the callback gets the
//                  Connection + Stmt only)
//   * `Close`    — Connection closed
//
// We model the surface — the actual hook firing happens inside the
// L4 interpreter + L7 façade.
//
// Submodules:
//   * `event`     — TraceEvent sum + mask flags
//   * `payload`   — per-event payload records
//   * `handler`   — TraceHandler protocol + chain composition
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.trace;

public module event;
public module payload;
public module handler;
